    // event_tx is dropped, so browser_events sender count decreases
});
```

When the thread exits, `event_tx` (which is a clone of the browser_events sender) gets dropped. The main sender is held by `ProcessManager::browser_events`. So `browser_events.recv()` returns `None` only when BOTH:
1. All bridge threads have exited (all renderers disconnected)
2. The process manager's browser_events is dropped

This would only happen during full shutdown. So for crash recovery, we need a different approach.

The simplest crash detection: in the bridge thread, when `rx_from_renderer.recv()` fails, send a `BrowserMessage::CloseTab` or a new `BrowserMessage::RendererCrashed` message.

